## What NOT To Do

**Never:**
- Use `pip` (use `uv`)
- Commit to main directly
- Force push protected branches
- Interactive git (`-i` flag)
- Create files unless necessary

**Avoid:**
- Over-engineering
- "Just in case" error handling
- Refactoring while fixing bugs
- Comments that repeat code
